Queries Performed & Key Insights
Filter companies by industry & employee size

Identified technology or finance companies with more than 10,000 employees.

Insight: Shows industries with high workforce concentration.

Healthcare benefits availability

Found companies that do not provide healthcare benefits.

Insight: Helps identify companies lacking essential employee support programs.

Revenue per employee calculation

Calculated revenue per employee and filtered companies exceeding $500k per employee.

Insight: Highlights industries/companies with high operational efficiency.

Maternity leave categorization

Used CASE to classify companies as Excellent, Good, or Poor based on maternity leave weeks.

Insight: Useful for HR benchmarking and workplace benefits analysis.

Employee distribution with healthcare benefits

Counted total employees in industries offering healthcare benefits.

Insight: Shows which industries prioritize employee welfare.

Average employee tenure analysis

Found industries where average tenure exceeds 7 years.

Insight: Indicates industries with stable and long-term employment trends.

Paid time off (PTO) analysis

Determined industries with more than 2 companies offering more than 20 PTO days.

Insight: Identifies employee-friendly sectors in terms of leave policies.

Top revenue-generating industries (with benefits)

Ranked top 3 industries by total revenue where healthcare benefits are provided.

Insight: Connects financial performance with employee benefits policies.

Average revenue per employee (industry level)

Found industries with an average revenue per employee > $500,000.

Insight: Highlights high-productivity industries.

Maternity leave risk categorization

Counted companies with zero maternity leave weeks and categorized industries as High Risk, Moderate Risk, or Low Risk.

Insight: Helps policymakers and HR professionals focus on industries needing workplace improvements.

Conclusion
These queries demonstrate how SQL can be used for:

Filtering and categorization (WHERE, CASE, IN, NOT IN)

Aggregations (SUM, AVG, COUNT)

Group-level analysis (GROUP BY + HAVING)

Ranking and filtering (ORDER BY, LIMIT)

This analysis provides actionable insights for HR, finance, and industry analysts to understand workplace policies and productivity trends.



CREATE TABLE fortune_companies (
    company_id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
    company_name TEXT,
    industry TEXT,
    revenue REAL,
    employees INTEGER,
    healthcare_benefits BIT,
    paid_time_off_days INTEGER,
    maternity_leave_weeks INTEGER,
    avg_employee_tenure REAL
);

